<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1785,2028]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,573]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="298" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,446,1785,1812]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is described based only in 
<specimenCount box="[946,1100,1786,1812]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
due to the low density, represented by the number of specimens collected in the Malaise trap, however, with the morphological characteristics presented in the description section there is no doubt about its identity. In the key to males of Neotropical 
<taxonomicName pageId="2" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">Limnophyes</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pinho, L. C. &amp; Andersen, T." box="[320,599,1894,1921]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" pagination="137 - 144" refId="ref3056" refString="Pinho, L. C. &amp; Andersen, T. (2015) Limnophyes guarani sp. n. a new hygropetric Orthocladiinae from southern Brazil (Diptera: Chironomidae). Zootaxa, 3948 (1), 137 - 144. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3948.1.9" type="journal article" year="2015">Pinho &amp; Andersen 2015</bibRefCitation>
), the new species key to couplet 6: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Edwards, 1931)" baseAuthorityName="Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[1005,1373,1894,1920]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Limnophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subnudicolis">
<emphasis box="[1005,1178,1894,1920]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">L. subnudicolis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Edwards, F. W." box="[1193,1365,1894,1920]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" pagination="233 - 331" refId="ref2688" refString="Edwards, F. W. (1931) Chironomidae. In: Diptera of Patagonia and South Chile II (5). Trustees of the British Museum, Natural History, London, pp, 233 - 331." type="book chapter" year="1931">Edwards, 1931</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,262,1930,1956]" name="Argentina" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">Argentina</collectingCountry>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Sublette &amp; Sasa, 1994" authorityName="Sublette &amp; Sasa" authorityYear="1994" box="[317,680,1930,1956]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Limnophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mariae">
<emphasis box="[317,425,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">L. mariae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sublette, J. E. &amp; Sasa, M." box="[432,680,1930,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" pagination="1 - 60" refId="ref3493" refString="Sublette, J. E. &amp; Sasa, M. (1994) Chironomidae collected in Onchocerciasis endemic areas in Guatemala (Insecta, Diptera). Spixiana, 20 (Supplement), 1 - 60. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631293 X 00316" type="journal article" year="1994">Sublette &amp; Sasa, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[748,873,1930,1956]" name="Guatemala" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
. However, 
<taxonomicName authority="Dantas &amp; Ramos-Pastrana &amp; Hamada, 2022" authorityName="Dantas &amp; Ramos-Pastrana &amp; Hamada" authorityYear="2022" box="[998,1221,1930,1956]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Limnophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="llanero" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[998,1221,1930,1956]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">Limnophyes llanero</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1227,1290,1930,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1227,1290,1930,1956]" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has six setae on epimeron II and the gonostylus has a well-developed, apical crista dorsalis, while 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1931" box="[1131,1305,1966,1992]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Limnophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="297" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subnudicolis">
<emphasis box="[1131,1305,1966,1992]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="297">L. subnudicolis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lacks setae on epimeron II and has a low crista dorsalis placed medially. Antenna with 13 flagellomeres and a well-developed crista dorsalis differentiates the new species from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sublette &amp; Sasa" authorityYear="1994" box="[706,814,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Limnophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mariae">
<emphasis box="[706,814,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">L. mariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has an antenna with 12 flagellomeres and a very weak crista dorsalis. In the key to the Nearctic species provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Saether, O. A." box="[894,1060,186,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="1029 - 1056" refId="ref3237" refString="Saether, O. A. (1975) Twelve new species of Limnophyes Eaton, with keys to Nearctic males of the genus (Diptera: Chironomidae). The Canadian Entomologist, 107, 1029 - 1056. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / Ent 1071029 - 10" type="journal article" year="1975">Saether (1975)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Dantas &amp; Ramos-Pastrana &amp; Hamada, 2022" authorityName="Dantas &amp; Ramos-Pastrana &amp; Hamada" authorityYear="2022" box="[1071,1180,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Limnophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="llanero" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1071,1180,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">L. llanero</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1186,1248,187,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1186,1248,187,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
key to at couplet 12, not matching any of the alternatives, mainly due to the absence of setae on preepisternum. The Nearctic species 
<taxonomicName authority="Saether, 1975" authorityName="Saether" authorityYear="1975" box="[151,486,258,285]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Limnophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristatissimus">
<emphasis box="[151,334,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">L. cristatissimus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Saether, O. A." box="[340,486,258,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="1029 - 1056" refId="ref3237" refString="Saether, O. A. (1975) Twelve new species of Limnophyes Eaton, with keys to Nearctic males of the genus (Diptera: Chironomidae). The Canadian Entomologist, 107, 1029 - 1056. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / Ent 1071029 - 10" type="journal article" year="1975">Saether, 1975</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
also has the gonostylus apically widened with a large crista dorsalis, but the presence of setae on the preepisternum, absence of lanceolate humerals and a rounded anal point separate the two species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Dantas &amp; Ramos-Pastrana &amp; Hamada, 2022" authorityName="Dantas &amp; Ramos-Pastrana &amp; Hamada" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Limnophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="llanero" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1414,1430,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,231,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">llanero</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[238,300,331,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[238,294,331,357]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">sp. n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
lacks setae on preepisternum, has lanceolate humerals and a cone-shaped anal point. When reviewing the species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Eaton" authorityYear="1875" box="[311,446,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Limnophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[311,446,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Limnophyes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Holarctic and Afrotropical regions, 
<bibRefCitation author="Saether, O. A." box="[955,1127,367,393]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="305 - 319" refId="ref3322" refString="Saether, O. A. (1990 a) A review of the genus Limnophyes Eaton from the Holarctic and Afrotropical regions. Entomologica Scandinavica, 21, 305 - 319. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631290 X 00229" type="journal article" year="1990">Saether (1990a)</bibRefCitation>
provided generic diagnosis and descriptions, discussed the phylogeny, and proposed species groups for the genus. Notwithstanding the volsella and virga of 
<taxonomicName authority="Dantas &amp; Ramos-Pastrana &amp; Hamada, 2022" authorityName="Dantas &amp; Ramos-Pastrana &amp; Hamada" authorityYear="2022" box="[293,402,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Limnophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="llanero" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[293,402,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">L. llanero</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[409,472,439,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[409,466,439,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">sp. n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
having shapes that resemble those found in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[1009,1104,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Limnophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minimus">
<emphasis box="[1009,1104,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">minimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group of 
<bibRefCitation author="Saether, O. A." box="[1216,1390,439,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="305 - 319" refId="ref3322" refString="Saether, O. A. (1990 a) A review of the genus Limnophyes Eaton from the Holarctic and Afrotropical regions. Entomologica Scandinavica, 21, 305 - 319. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 187631290 X 00229" type="journal article" year="1990">Saether (1990a)</bibRefCitation>
, the absence of preepisternals and the strongly enlarged, apical crista dorsalis, the new species differ from the diagnosis of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Meigen" baseAuthorityYear="1818" box="[226,321,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Chironomidae" genus="Limnophyes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minimus">
<emphasis box="[226,321,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">minimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-group, which is characterized by preepisternum with an anterior row of setae and a pointed crista dorsalis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
